The paper deals with a security challenge in wireless networks, specifically the fake base station attack. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The proposed countermeasures involve utilizing location information, which suggests the involvement of information theory (cs.IT) and possibly software engineering (cs.SE) for implementation. The use of signal strength and cooperation also suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY).
